<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,153,503]" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,369,395]" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species is easy to differentiate from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[871,1009,370,395]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[871,1009,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">Heteragrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1129,1239,369,395]" name="Colombia" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">Colombia</collectingCountry>
by its completely black head (
<figureCitation box="[286,372,404,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1465,1490]" captionTargetBox="[359,1216,453,1446]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[359,1227,453,1446]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Face color pattern: H. calendulum (taken from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez 2017): (A) male Pueblo Rico, Risaralda (B) female Pueblo Rico, Risaralda. Heteragrion demarmelsi: (C) male Leticia, Amazonas (D) female Leticia, Amazo- nas. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: (E) male Union Panamericana, Chocó (F) female Union Panamericana, Chocó. Heteragrion flavidorsum: (G) male PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (H) female PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo. H. inca: (I) male Puerto Legui- zamo, Putumayo (J) female Puerto Leguizamo, Putumayo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415709/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
), red abdomen in males, female intersternite with a rounded dorsal plate (
<figureCitation box="[1192,1293,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
), and genital valves not reaching distal border of S10 (
<figureCitation box="[619,724,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). We report it here for the first time from 
<collectingRegion box="[1197,1281,441,467]" country="Colombia" name="Boyaca" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">Boyacá</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion country="Colombia" name="Valle del Cauca" pageId="14" pageNumber="104">Valle del Cauca</collectingRegion>
Departments.
</paragraph>
